This is the protocol for a review and there is no abstract. The objectives are as follows:, The objective of this systematic review is to develop estimates on the benefits of preventive treatment with hormone replacement therapy (HRT) for osteoporosis, taken for long term in postmenopausal women., We will test the following hypothesis: the use of HRT slows bone loss and has a beneficial effect on the axial and appendicular bone density, thus preventing fractures of women in menopause